I cleared all the azure instances from my docker config, updated `az`, and tried to get this to work from a clean slate and it still didn't produce that critical `credHelpers` entry:
```
(base) dking@wm28c-761 hail % az version  
{
  "azure-cli": "2.48.1",
  "azure-cli-core": "2.48.1",
  "azure-cli-telemetry": "1.0.8",
  "extensions": {}
}
(base) dking@wm28c-761 hail % az acr login -n haildev.azurecr.io
The login server endpoint suffix '.azurecr.io' is automatically omitted.
Login Succeeded
(base) dking@wm28c-761 hail % cat ~/.docker/config.json
{
	"auths": {
		"haildev.azurecr.io": {},
		"https://index.docker.io/v1/": {}
	},
	"credsStore": "desktop",
	"credHelpers": {
		"asia.gcr.io": "gcloud",
		"eu.gcr.io": "gcloud",
		"gcr.io": "gcloud",
		"marketplace.gcr.io": "gcloud",
